ematorsk train station attack','More than 50 people were killed and many more wounded in a missile strike on a train station in the eastern city of Kramatorsk on Friday. One day later, people are attempting to pick up the pieces from the deadly attack.','https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-61055105','2022-04-10 01:30:00'),(2579,8,2,1,NULL,'Ukraine: Johnson pledges aid to Zelensky in Kyiv meeting','Mr Johnson\'s visit to Kyiv was not announced in advance and the first indication he was in the city came when a photograph of his meeting with President Zelensky was put on Twitter by the Ukrainian embassy in London.','https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-61052643','2022-04-09 23:33:00'),(2580,8,2,1,NULL,'Ukraine: Inside the spies’ attempts to stop the war','Traditionally, it is the job of a spy to keep secrets - but as the invasion of Ukraine loomed, Western intelligence officials made the unusual decision to tell the world what they knew.','https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-61044063','2022-04-09 03:34:00'),(2581,8,2,1,NULL,'Inside Chernobyl: We stole Russian fuel to prevent catastrophe','The former nuclear power plant at Chernobyl in northern Ukraine was taken over by Russian forces on the first day of the invasion. It\'s now back under Ukraine\'s control. The BBC\'s Yogita Limaye is among the first journalists to look inside it since the Ru','https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-61048256','2022-04-09 07:36:00'),(2582,8,2,1,NULL,'Ukraine, the UN and history\'s greatest broken promise','Accounts of atrocities committed by Russian troops against Ukrainian civilians are emerging daily. There are calls for President Putin and others to be prosecuted for war crimes - but how likely is that to happen?','https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-61021862','2022-04-10 05:38:00'),(2583,51,2,1,NULL,'Ukraine war: Boris Johnson meets Volodymyr Zelesnkyy in Kyiv to offer more military and financial aid ','The Ukrainian defence ministry tweeted: \"We welcome Boris Johnson in Kyiv, the firs